Three men were shot on a Bronx street corner Friday evening, police said. Shots rang out around 8:40 p.m. at White Plains Road and Lafayette Avenue in the Soundview section, according to the NYPD. The victims were in stable condition at Jacobi Medical Center, where they were all “highly uncooperative” with investigators, police said. The circumstance surrounding the violence was unclear. Police didn’t immediately provide a suspect description.